Upon review of banking and financial mathematics standards, compound interest calculations operate under the formula: 

I = P(1 + r/n)^(nt) - P, where:
- I denotes interest accrued;
- P represents initial principal amount;
- r signifies the annual interest rate (as decimal);
- n symbolizes the compounding frequency (e.g., 12 for monthly);
- t is the time in years.

This calculation model incorporates exponential growth in accumulated interest and is standardized in international accounting practices.
